comments: Wright (MEM) briefly places a legal forearm to LaVine  (CHI) during his drive, but does not affect his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (CHI) places a legal forearm to Bradley's (MEM) side before blocking his shot.
Porter Jr. (CHI) makes contact with the ball prior to Bradley's (MEM) shot attempt hitting the backboard.
RATR shows that Conley (MEM) engages with Markkanen (CHI) during Dunn's drive. RATR shows that he tugs at Markkanen's hip concurrent with the whistle on the shooting foul.
RAR shows Markkanen (CHI) legally establishes himself in Conley's (MEM) path during the pick.
[Observable in enhanced video] Frame by frame from RATR shows that Dunn (CHI) hops on his left foot after he gathers the ball.
RAR shows Caboclo (MEM) makes contact to Dunn's (CHI) shoulder when he attempts to block the shot and then comes down on his arms.
Noah (MEM) releases from the pick on Dunn (CHI) with an extended arm, but does not dislodge or reroute him.
LLB shows Dunn (CHI) makes leg contact with Conley (MEM) during Conley's upward shooting motion.
RLB shows Conley (MEM) makes marginal contact with Dunn (CHI) that doesn't affect his ability to receive the inbound pass.
Conley (MEM) makes marginal contact with LaVine (CHI) at the start of LaVine's drive and does not affect his SQBR.
Noah (MEM) and Lopez (CHI) engage and disengage during the shot as both players try to secure rebounding position.
RAR and RHH show Porter Jr. (CHI) is not established in Wright's (MEM) path and makes contact with his wrist during his shot attempt.
Lopez (CHI) is firming up in Wright's path (MEM) before the contact.
Following the screen, Dunn (CHI) has a resting forearm on Noah (MEM) and does not dislodge or reroute him. He then cleanly knocks the pass away.
Noah (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dunn (CHI) and does not deliver any contact to Dunn.
Dunn (CHI) and Conley (MEM) engage and disengage off-ball.
Multiple angles reviewed.  Porter Jr. (CHI) jumps to Holiday's (MEM) side and either makes slight contact with the ball or misses it on his attempted block.
Noah (MEM) and Lopez (CHI) engage and disengage and separate during the rebound.

RATR and R-Slash show that Valanciunas (MEM) initially establishes a legal screening position in Dunn's (CHI) path, but then continues to reestablish his position and delivers contact that dislodges Dunn.
Noah (MEM) commits a take foul on Markkanen (CHI).
The illegal contact by Valanciunas (MEM) dislodges Dunn (CHI) into Conley (MEM), causing him to lose his balance.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Since no players touch the ball on the inbound pass by MEM, the ball is awarded to CHI.
Conley (MEM) makes marginal contact with Markkanen (CHI), but does not affect his SQBR.
Conley (MEM) commits a take foul on Porter Jr. (CHI)
Markkanen (CHI) makes slight arm contact with Conley (MEM), but does not prevent Conley from releasing the pass.
Valanciunas (MEM) commits a take foul on Markkanen (CHI).
